<p>Always use <code>fieldset</code> tag for grouping checkboxes and radios, native <code>fieldset</code> tag
    has an <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/fieldset" target="_blank">additional benefits</a>.
</p>

<h2>Basic form</h2>
<p>If you need multiline label beside checkbox (or radio) use the additional <code>span</code> tag</p>

<div class="code-example">
    <div data-clone>
        <form>
            <div class="row">
                <label>Text field</label>
                <input type="text" placeholder="First name">
            </div>

            <div class="row">
                <label>Select</label>
                <select>
                    <option value="0">---</option>
                    <option value="1">Option 1</option>
                    <option value="2">Option 2</option>
                    <option value="3">Option 3</option>
                </select>
            </div>

            <div class="row">
                <label>Textarea</label>
                <textarea rows="3"></textarea>
            </div>

            <fieldset>
                <legend>Checkboxes</legend>
                <div class="row">
                    <label>
                        <input type="checkbox" checked>
                        Checked by default first checkbox
                    </label>
                </div>

                <div class="row">
                    <label>
                        <input type="checkbox">
                        Second checkbox
                    </label>
                </div>
            </fieldset>

            <fieldset>
                <legend>Radio buttons</legend>
                <div class="row">
                    <label>
                        <input type="radio" name="form-radios">
                        First radio
                    </label>
                </div>

                <div class="row">
                    <label>
                        <input type="radio" name="form-radios">
                        <span>Fusce commodo aliquam arcu. Pellentesque egestas, neque sit amet convallis pulvinar, <br>
                        justo nulla eleifend augue, ac auctor orci leo non est. Praesent turpis. Suspendisse faucibus, <br>
                        nunc et pellentesque egestas, lacus ante convallis tellus, vitaeiaculis lacus elit id tortor.
                        </span>
                    </label>
                </div>
            </fieldset>

            <div class="row">
                <p class="legend">Attachments</p>
                <input type="file">
            </div>

            <button type="submit" class="btn btn--block">Submit</button>
        </form>
    </div>

    <pre lang="html"></pre>
</div>


<h2>Form divided by columns</h2>
<p>Add class <code>.grid</code> to the form and use standard grid columns as wrapper for fields.</p>

<div class="code-example">
    <div data-clone>
        <form class="grid">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-6">
                    <label>First name</label>
                    <input type="text">
                </div>
                <div class="col-6">
                    <label>Options</label>
                    <select>
                        <option value="0">---</option>
                        <option value="1">Option 1</option>
                        <option value="2">Option 2</option>
                        <option value="3">Option 3</option>
                    </select>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-12">
                    <label>Email</label>
                    <input type="text">
                </div>
            </div>

            <fieldset>
                <legend>Checkboxes</legend>
                <div class="row">
                    <label>
                        <input type="checkbox" checked>
                        Checked by default first checkbox
                    </label>
                </div>

                <div class="row">
                    <label>
                        <input type="checkbox">
                        Second checkbox
                    </label>
                </div>
            </fieldset>
        </form>
    </div>

    <pre lang="html"></pre>
</div>

<h2>Disabling fields</h2>
<p>Use <code>disabled</code> parameters on tag <code>fieldset</code> to disable group of fields.</p>
<div class="code-example">
    <div>
        <form data-clone>
            <div class="row">
                <label>Text field</label>
                <input type="text" placeholder="First name" disabled>
            </div>

            <fieldset disabled>
                <p class="legend">Disabled specific field</p>

                <div class="row">
                    <label>
                        <input type="checkbox" checked>
                        Checkbox 1
                    </label>
                </div>

                <div class="row">
                    <label>
                        <input type="checkbox">
                        Checkbox 2
                    </label>
                </div>

                <div class="row">
                    <label>
                        <input type="checkbox">
                        Checkbox 3
                    </label>
                </div>
            </fieldset>
        </form>
    </div>

    <pre lang="html"></pre>
</div>

